  "prompt": "What you will do if your boyfriend is cheating on you?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry that you're going through this. Dealing with infidelity is extremely painful, and it's important to take care of yourself during this time. Here's a list of steps you might consider taking if you suspect or find out your partner is cheating:\n\n1. **Gather Evidence**: Ensure you have concrete evidence before confronting your partner. Jumping to conclusions without clear proof can lead to unnecessary stress and conflict.\n\n2. **Self-Reflection**: Take time to think about what you want and how you feel. This will help you approach the situation with a clear mind.\n\n3. **Confrontation**: Have a calm and honest discussion with your partner about your suspicions and any evidence you have. Clear communication is key.\n\n4. **Seeking Support**: Talk to friends, family, or a therapist about your situation. Having support from others can be invaluable.\n\n5. **Evaluate the Relationship**: Consider whether you want to continue the relationship. Reflect on whether trust can be rebuilt and if you both are willing to work on it.\n\n6. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to stay, establish clear boundaries and expectations moving forward. Trust takes time to restore and requires effort from both partners.\n\n7. **Self-Care**: Focus on your own well-being. Engage in activities that bring you joy and comfort, and give yourself time to heal.\n\n8. **Consider Professional Help**: Couples counseling can be a constructive way to address issues and rebuild trust if you both decide to stay in the relationship.\n\nRemember, everyone's situation is unique, and you should do what feels right for you.",
